 />&gt; build fails<br />&gt;<br />&gt; &gt;&gt; arch/arm/include/asm/irq.h:34:50: error: unknown type name 'cpumask_t'<br />&gt;     extern void arch_trigger_cpumask_backtrace(const cpumask_t *mask,<br /><br />Yes. Please just add a forward declaration of 'struct cpumask', and<br />change that cpumask_t to use that instead.<br /><br />I'm not sure we need to remove it entirely (there's a fair number of<br />users), but we can/should deprecate it, and certainly use 'struct<br />cpumask' in function declarations etc so that you don't need to go<br />through some include file hell.<br /><br />           Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
